cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.NE

The paper discusses the extraction and analysis of eye movement features during reading, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely sub-category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) as the study can provide valuable tools for human-computer interaction. Computer Vision (cs.CV) is also likely as eye tracking is a common technique used in computer vision research. Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) is another possibility as eye movements during reading can provide insights into language processing. Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) are also possible as the study involves the analysis of large datasets and the quantification of test-retest reliability, which are common topics in these sub-fields.
